cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. 

The paper addresses the problem of finding descriptive explanations of facts stored in a knowledge graph, which involves information retrieval, natural language processing, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, and uses machine learning to extract facts from a corpus, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories.
